import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    yearly_disasters = data.groupby('Year').size().reset_index(name='Count')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=yearly_disasters, x='Year', y='Count')
    plt.title('What is the trend of natural disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Natural Disasters')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    
    total_deaths_by_disaster = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Entity', y='Deaths', data=total_deaths_by_disaster)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('Which type of natural disaster has caused the most deaths?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Deaths', bins=50, kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    median_deaths = data['Deaths'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_deaths, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_deaths:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Deaths')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by natural disasters?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    yearly_avg_deaths = data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=yearly_avg_deaths)
    plt.axhline(yearly_avg_deaths['Deaths'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {yearly_avg_deaths['Deaths'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths caused by natural disasters per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Deaths')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    disaster_counts = data.groupby(['Entity', 'Year']).size().reset_index(name='Frequency')
    disaster_deaths = data.groupby(['Entity', 'Year'])['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()

    merged_data = pd.merge(disaster_counts, disaster_deaths, on=['Entity', 'Year'])

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    scatter_plot = sns.scatterplot(data=merged_data, x='Frequency', y='Deaths', hue='Entity')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the frequency of natural disasters and the number of deaths caused?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Disaster Type', loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
